-- Qatari Stocks Surge as Much as 7.8% as Country Wins Bid to Host World Cup
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2010-12-05T07:07:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-05/qatari-stocks-surge-as-much-as-7-8-as-country-wins-bid-to-host-world-cup.html
Qatari stocks jumped as much as 7.8
percent in early trading after the country won the rights to
host the 2022 soccer World Cup.  The benchmark index surged 7.7 percent to 8,818.64, the
highest intraday level since October 2008, at 10:06 a.m. in
Doha. All 20 shares in the gauge advanced.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
